lly spread out.The Jetpack and glider were my bread and butter for transportation.The storyline wasn't anything special at first, although they threw a few interesting curve balls and twists. I felt like the game ended in a satisfying way, although the overall experience felt like something was missing. Honestly I'd love to see what this game company can do with their second Planet Explorer game.Performance. I had no problem running on max settings, although I noticed that regardless of my settings when NPC colonists would sleep for the night the game were stutter and freeze with performance issues. Upon looking online it looks like this is a fairly common problem.The colony system is an interesting one. They are actually useful at maintaining your colony and will do a variety of tasks. Although the AI isn't very good, NPC would often hangout underwater or walk off tall buildings/cliffs. Various machines that you can build inside your colony have different functions; some of those functions are finished while other's I suspect will be changed in future patches.Although this review is full of criticisms that game is fun, the storyline can be interesting and underneathe all the flaws the game is really amazing. But there's alot of flaws, you need patience to play this game.At first I recommend this in the review and then after a few days comtempllation I reversed my recommendation. It's a great game at it's foundation, but it's not there yet. If the game was still in early access my review would be different. I realize that although I did have fun, it's not likely that I'll replay the game again."
