76561198005757129,Recommended,237870,33082224,Posted: 1 July,all,Dovahbear,"One of the better games I've played in recent years, it does however suffer from bugs and some clumsy UI elements. After a fair amount of play time I am inclined to say the developers ambition exceeded their grasp slightly, but overall they produced a fun game that is distinguished in its genre. I had a wonderful experience that was well worth the price to me.Notable negatives:There are bugs to be found in this game but nothing I couldn't live with. As an old school gamer I have it deeply ingrained in me to save often and that served me well for the odd instance where I encountered a bug. I knew going in the developer was a modest and unproven studio so I didn't expect otherwise, so an occassional bug which requires a reload from a prior save was fine by me. I note this however as while it may be fine for me, it may not be fine for you.Most of my time played was single player and that was great. Online play on official servers was not nearly as great. While not terrible, overall server performance was just a lackluster experience for me causing just enough irriation with lag, etc. that it prevented me from fully enjoying myself. The greatest potential for this game is in the multiplayer which made it a bit of a shame that the offical servers just didn't quite perform well enough for me to stay interested in spending time on them. Privately hosted multiplayer I think could be great fun.Positives to ponder and other postulations:More than anything I love the atmosphere of this game, kind of like the equivilant of a ""feel good"" movie without getting overly sappy. It walks a fine line that does justice to the concept of a survival situation in a sci-fi environment while keeping the tone light hearted. In many respects it reminded me of old school sci-fi in how it lets the narrative carry its own weight in that sense. For me at least this was something I want to really applaud this game for, it's something it really got right that I think isn't easy.Story wise, I won't tell you it's Isaac Asimov, but it's FAR better than I expected. Quite frankly my expectations here were pretty low, so I was pleasantly surprised at how well thought out and complex the story was.I also found the audio to be better than I would have thought. While the title song is a bit cheesy for my taste, there's no denying the quality is far beyond what I would have ever expected from a small studio game like this. Likewise goes with in game ambiant sounds and music. The sound track to the game is absolutely well done, beautiful and way beyond anything I would have expected from a game of this scale.Mechanically, the game does a whole lot of things right if a bit clumsily. Building and crafting could be a little more intuitive, but I quickly forgave that as the system is really great in allowing you to make veritably anything you can conceive. The ability to save and share creations via ISO files is a great addition that brings a lot of life into the crafting and creative aspect of the game. My criticism of any of it would be the same, execution fell a little short of the intention. It does however work well enough that despite the quirks I can easily say it's one of the best crafting systems I've ever had the pleasure to play with. I think it's absolutely underrated how forward thinking the system is, veritably everything a gamer who loves crafting could want. Again, it's clumsy at points and that's a shame, but it's still a great idea that manages to work.Closing thoughts:I think the bugs and clumsiness found early on turn people off before they discover the rich experience underneath. I understand where a lot of reviews are coming from and I can't really blame them, as much as I have enjoyed the game it does suffer from a lack polish. I really do believe the studio is on to something great and I hope they'll consider giving this title the polish it needs to spruce it up for DLC or a sequel."
,Recommended,237870,12490348,"Posted: 14 October, 2014",all,Princess Goddammit,"This is quite a nice game, even for Early Release. It is very pretty and in build mode you can do just about everything. The ISO creation system is fun to work with and fairly easy to get the hang of. You can design just about any vehicle, sword, or other weapon you can think of to have fun with. I have not played them but Adventure and Story mode also seem to have much to offer if that is what you are looking for.The game does have some issues with lag and charactar control but the dev team seems to be working on the game and are good about keeping players informed about what they are doing and where they are going. I can reccomend this game very highly even though it is still EA."
