,Recommended,237870,9554425,"Posted: 18 March, 2014",all,Chinspinner,"Note: I originally had this as a thumbs down, but the creation kit has changed my mind.This game has great potential, but has a number of issues associated with its alpha state.The game basically has four play modes: -- Story; which does exactly what it says on the tin.- Adventure; in which you jump into the world with some friendly NPC's and the foundations of a settlement to build upon once you have collected the prerequisite materials.- Build; in which you are given free reign and unlimited materials to build whatever you want.- Multi-player; in which you can set up a server with friends/ family.The Bad: -The combat is sluggish, locks you into animations and largely involves swinging a stick in the general vicinity of monsters.The controls for vehicles (especially helicopters) need a rework (they are simply poorly realised currently).The build and multi-player modes barely work, the map in build mode has such short draw distances that the use of any vehicle results in you driving off the edge of the map and dieing.The story mode is the most complete, but it does involve some needless time sinks, and needs a lot more polish.  It also stops part way through while the remainder is in development- but provides circa 20 hours of gameplay currently.The Good: -The story mode is fun (but is orientated towards gathering and crafting).The creation system, in which you can design weapons and vehicles (wheel based or rotor based), is the high point of the game.  Certain pre-made items are required such as a cockpit or energy cells, but beyond this you can create almost anything you set your mind upon.  Of course to use these items in game (other than in the buggy build mode) you will need to collect the materials first.  There are limitations to the system, for example, building a vast rectangle with rotors all over it will give you better overall stats than taking the time to build a realistic, aerodynamic chopper.  Look at the time I have spent in game, most of them have been spent in the creation system.  If this appeals to you, this game is worth buying.In conclusion; this is clearly an alpha game, and as such it lacks a lot of polish and features, and is fairly buggy.  Once the development has progressed it should be great fun."
