76561197970382100,Recommended,237870,9825429,"Posted: 15 April, 2014",all,Dragnet,"After a couple of less-than-stellar experiences with alpha/early-access/kickstarter games, I was pretty much set in the ""never again"" camp. A friend told me that I _really_ should check out Planet Explorer, given he knew how much I love sandbox games.This game - even at the alpha stage is, to put it mildly, absolutely amazing. Many, many years ago, an essay was written in the MMO community called ""Let me bake bread"" - in short, it said a _great_ video game lets the player play as _they_ want: Be that fighting, building, exploring, crafting or socializing. This game has it all (well, maybe not quite the socializing, but I haven't played multiplayer).The visuals are beautiful; The build system is limited only by your imagination and the content in the game - again, even at this early stage - reinforces both the suspension of disbelief and wonder.I could not be more pleased with this game. If you are a sandbox game lover, you will not go wrong with Planet Explorer."
