76561197998500981,Recommended,237870,32326120,Posted: 10 June,all,maelxp,"For me, it is quite difficult to decide on this game.Do I like this game? Yes, absolutely.Could it be better? Yes, absolutely.Do I recommend it? Kinda...Lets go into detail:I have bought this game quite a while ago and played only the story mode (as it was pretty much the only thing working back than, even though the story wasn't finished). Back than only a few quests and only a ""small"" part of the map was accessible (I say ""small"" here, but it still took like 10-15 minutes to walk from the east edge to the west edge of the map).This meant, that I played the relatively few quests several times and gotten used to them.Unfortunately, new players obviously don't do that, they (logically) want to play the story in one go... and this - I think - is one of the reasons, why new players have issues with this game. To me it feels like, this game was optimized for players already familiar with the game mechanics - for players that took the time to just play around for hours and tested everything out.The game gives players a lot of options - without explaining how to use them best. That's up to the player to figure out.One example: The building system.You get two types of blocks (voxel blocks and blocks) - no explanation what the actual difference is... just figure it out for yourself.Then you can pick the type of material - again, no explanation what the difference between them is. Also no explanation, why you can use some type of materials (like diamond) and not others (like titanium).If you chose voxel blocks, you can pick texture, if you chose normal blocks, you can pick one of several shapes.Once you have set all that up, you can start, right?Well, no. You have to make sure there is nothing in the way of your building, so no peacefull animals, no NPCs, no piles of dung (seems so irrelevant, but especially on larger builds, dung lying around is SO annoying) and especially no enemies or aggressive animals... because they will obviously ♥♥♥♥ things up - and again on larger builds, it is pretty much impossible to not be interrupted several times because of attacking animals.And I haven't even started on the clunkyness of the camera during building...As for the creation system:(For those unfamiliar: The game has an editor in-game, where you can create various stuff, like vehicles, weapons and decorative objects - all based on voxels, objects can be saved and reused in other replays or be shared with others)The interface is somewhat difficult to learn, but once you get the hang of it, it is acutally quite fun to use and relevant to the game. For example, I created a rifle that is way better than the early models available in game and also cheaper to produce. I can use that rifle in every replay now. The only issue here is, that you can not repair it unless you have a colony set up...One thing I do however not understand about the editor: Why can't we use glass (or transparent materials in general)??In short / TL:DR:Planet Explorers is a fun game, if you like to figure things out for yourself and are not easily frustrated, if it doesn't work as you expect it to. There is pretty much no limit to your creativity here, especially with the creation system.However: The game does have bugs (both in quests and the base systems itself), that make it very hard to really enjoy it in the long term."
