,Recommended,237870,33674985,Posted: 20 July,all,Wark Maugh,"This game is fun in its current state and has fantastic potential for its completion. It includes elements from many games which helps garner familiarity with the basic structure of the game. While some say that ""copying"" from other games is distasteful, I think this game does it with class and makes its own unique version. The gameplay is enticing with a great work to reward ratio. Play with friends for an absolute blast!This game features a fully destructable environment, but not so much with weapons or explosives -- just by mining and cutting down trees. You can dig a big looping circle underground if you desire. You can open a build menu instantly and build a giant wall out of different materials specifying lengths of the x,y,z axis. This makes structure creation simple, and customization endless. The crafting system is highly intuitive, it tells you the prequisites for the object you're trying to construct.There is creation function in this game where you can build almost anything, you choose whether it will be a vehicle (plane, car, or ship), weapon (gun, sword, etc), automated turret among many other things. The creation system has a Computer Assisted Drawing feel to it, albeit a simplistic version. You can choose a material and click to begin a rectangle and drag it out to set its x,y,z axis. You can make spheres, cylinders, triangles. It is very open ended.Cons: This game has a bit of a learning curve, especially in the vehicle creation system. I'd recommend modifying a template first to get used to the functionality of the system. Making a vehicle from scratch is immensely rewarding, but admittedly difficult especially with an airplane (the relationship between balance, thrust, and weight can be hard)"
