,Recommended,237870,27818362,"Posted: 27 November, 2016",all,Khronoe,"My friends and I have waited years to play this game because of it's time in early access but it was worth the wait, for us at least.  I'm normally not a fan of building or survival genre games but this one has captivated me.  We purchased the game at least two years ago and have tried it off and on since that time but didn't want to put in a lot of time until it was finished because we didn't want to have played it all and not be able to enjoy it when it released.  So here we are now and I'm glad we waited.  The game still have some minor issues that need resolve but the devs are so far handling those issues in short order.  The devs are also pretty responvie on the forums and seem genuinely interested in player feedback.What I love most about this game is it's versatility.  It has a great story mode that can be played in either single player, multiplayer or on a hosted server.  Mulitplayer games can also be co-op, survival or PvP and there is also an adventure mode which is an open world quest and dungeon crawler style map.  The maps outside of story mode are also all procedurely generated with dungeons, caves, etc.  in addition to that, the options for building are seemingly limitless.  You can build your own weapons, armor, VTOLs, ground vehicles, ships, submaries, personal robots and buildings.Plus the colony system is a lot of fun for me.  It's like having a small scale sim built into the game.  As you encounter NPCs in the game you can invite them to a colony that you establish and assign them certain roles.  They can be medics, workers that can repair, recyle or enhance gear, farmers and more.The in game editor is also very powerful yet fairly simple to master with a little time and patience.  I am still pretty impressed with what can be created on the fly without having to drop out of the game to create custom models and whatnot.  You can not only build the body of your design but also create custom materials using your own textures (based off of a default material), place your own decals on your items and more.There is also a world editor that I haven't attempted to use yet but for those who are into world building it seems like a great tool for custom scenarios.I really hope this game continues to grow and develop because it holds great potential and I can't recommend it enough for players who enjoy sandbox and open building games."
