,Recommended,237870,11798765,"Posted: 20 August, 2014",all,drw7,"This is the first review I've ever written and after playing more than 50 hours with Planet Explorers, I felt compelled to write this review.  First, the specs:  I'm playing the latest build, A0.831, on an i7-2600K, 16Gg RAM, and a GeForce 760 Ti.  I absolutely love playing Planet Explorers.  The combination of creativity, exploration, and surprises are what do it for me.  The huge world seems filled with so much potential and I'm constantly being pleased with the next ""big thing to do"".  The game is graphically beautiful, and I've only crashed maybe twice in the 50+ hours I've played it. The progression from simple tools and resources, to building a colony is smoothly done, such that I never feel overwhelmed.I enjoy building structures, fortifying them, defending them, and expanding them.  I've only played in Story mode and I like how the story expands the gameplay for you.Even though the game is Alpha, I highly recommend it.  I got this game on sale for $15.00 and have had over 50 hours of enjoyment from it.  How can you beat that deal?When I'm away from the game I find myself coming up with ideas for what I'll try and do next in Planet Explorers.For instance:  I made a crude heliocopter and was flying back to my colony one fine day when I was attacked by some dragon-like, vulture, flying creature.  He destroyed my helicopter!  So later on while having lunch, I thought ""I'm going to build a much bigger, attack chopper, with a front-mounted cannon.  I'll show that flying freak who's the boss!""It's these kinds of experiences both unscripted, and scripted, that keep me coming back to PE!"
