,Recommended,237870,11366777,"Posted: 22 July, 2014",all,DFJ,"Many things to like: lots of freedom, digging, very open world, quests, an engaging plot, building with both prefab and various blocks.Similarly crafting includes both classic recipe and freeform voxel-oriented forms, with more items being possible to craft freeform over time, as the devs find balanced rules for them.As with other early access games performance can be a bit sketchy in certain poorly optimized cases, but the game is entirely playable on the reccomended hardware.A few bugs, but this is not unexpected for early access.Because the game uses a bit more aggressive gpu computation, it will appreciate a flaky gpu less than some lucky games. This is likely to remain the case, and even become true of more other games as time passes anyway, though. :pPersonally, I'd prefer if the design editor felt more integrated with the game - right now it feels much more like a meta process which messes with one's feel of existing in the world a bit. not sure how much this can be improved, given that the editor needs to be usable from *outside* of play as well. I hope they find some sweet compromises, though. :)Overall I quite enjoyed the game in it's current state, and I look forward to playing it more as development progresses, and again whenever it releases."
