76561198083093314,Recommended,237870,14576923,"Posted: 21 February, 2015",all,The Silent Bard,"To express it in the shortest way I can, Planet Explorers is what Sony's Landmark should be.A little more in depth? This game combines the better mechanics of Runescape and Minecraft while still feeling like its own original game. This feeling most definately lends itself to the fantastic (however loud) and serene soundtrack; the plethera of monsters whose strength can warrant a knife or an organized battalion; and especially the creation tool: an interface allowing you to build items (swords, equipment, vehicles, airships, etc) directly into the game using voxels. No wrap-around, and no microtransactions needed; anyone can quite literally build (or download) for themselves anything they can imagine while in game.This last mechanic - the ability to create items ""like it ain't no thing"" is what really sets Planet Explorers up to be phenominal. Currently, the game is in Alpha 0.87, but the only bug my friends & I have come across is sleeping in a bed - a bug we first believed to be related to our own incompetence.I highly recomend Planet Explorers. Its mechanics sets it apart from the growing masses in this Sci-Fi genre and its emersion will keep you and your friends eager to play more."
