76561198007316160,Recommended,237870,14911774,"Posted: 15 March, 2015",all,Jim Bananas,"Brilliant game.  If you like open world sandbox with plenty to do to make real progress then this is for you.  The world is fantastic with a variety of environments to explore and monsters to kill.  You can carry an enormous amount of material so you do not have to spend your time running back to base to unload, the crafting system is easy and once you have set up your own colony you can design and build anything from motor bikes, planes, helicopters, vehicles, ships and weapons.The only downside is that the game does crash occasionally and a few of the missions require a bit of help from others but the community is active and helpful.This is a terrific game and although I have only played story mode I am thoroughly impressed and give it a score of 99%.Well done Devs :)"
,Recommended,237870,14686655,"Posted: 27 February, 2015",all,SupniX,"First off, I reccomend this game to anyone who even slightly enjoyed Minecraft or Terraria, espescially if you enjoyed the building aspect of the games. So what makes this game different?You create your own weapons, shields, vehicles, and decorations. I dont mean MMO-style crafting either, you literally build them from the ground up, voxel by voxel.A few quick warnings; This game does have bugs and glitches (ie, can't currently explore the northern half or so of the map without it crashing). As a side note, monsters and terrain have a bad habit of destroying your favorite vehicles. To solve both problems, save often.Lastly, I wanted to provide a few tips that I wish someone had shared with me.-There is a meteorite crater just north of where you start in story mode, It is full of Iron and Copper and is great for making money.-Almost straight west of the meteorite crater is a ""Rock Formation"" the vendors there sell you the scripts (crafting recipes) for a better pickaxe as well as the parts to make a land vehicle.-To the west of where you spawn (Past where the river forks along the coast) There is a vendor, he sells the items you need to make aircrafts.-Don't try hunting (for currency anyways) with bullets. With a few exceptions, you lose around the same amount you gain. Instead, try building up a vehicle with lots of firepower. As long as you have coal from mining, there really isn't any cost to refill the batteries on said vehicle.-(IMO) Build your vehicles out of Marble. It is easily the most abundant of the resources, making upgrades/repairs cheap. Also, my Marble helicopter currently has 55,000 durability after two upgrades. I will die before it does every time.tl;dr? Yes this game is amazing, no it isn't perfect. There are a few bugs that really need to get fixed, but the game is in alpha. Save often and I would easily give this game a 9/10."
