,Recommended,237870,14685169,"Posted: 27 February, 2015",all,Shadowalker,"Where to start. I'm playing the .87 alpha version and having a great time. There are plenty of bugs, some game breaking. These are planned to be fixed in the .9 update.  I've built all sorts of colonies: Hobbit colonies in the side of hills. A plateau colony; very defensible AND it makes a great spot for hang gliding. A cave colony which, sadly, crashed the game on me.Constructing vehicles is great fun.  I’ve designed one that was little more than a rocket and a cockpit which proceeded to disintegrate with me on it after a few meters. I’ve built a mountain crawling troop transport with 16 wheels.  Motorcycles and helicopters. I’ve been limited by my imagination and part number limits (i.e. 16 wheel limit).Mining can be fun or boring depending on your purpose. I spread my mining out between building and questing.  Mine for 4 hours straight and you’ll hate it.  Especially if your game crashes or gets hung up. Hint: don’t mine near water until the next patch your saves will get corrupted.Speaking of saves.  You have plenty of slots to use for saving your world.  This is really convienent since you hae three play modes to choose from.  Story is where it’s at for me.  I like having a story line in my games and objectives. Adventure mode is more of a sandbox only play. Build mode is great for building, testing, and saving your designs since there is unlimited resources. There is also a multiplayer component. Sorry to say I haven’t much tried that part of the game.Updates are a little slow. I want the full game now, but they can’t make that happen. So if you want it all complete and ready to play then wait to buy. Otherwise you’ll sink countless hours into this game and say to yourself and to any who’ll listen “when is the next *censored* update *censored* it!”  Another great thing is that the devs are active with the forum community so be heard!All said this is a very enjoyable game and I’ve spent more hours on it in alpha than I have with most of my release games.Maybe a little bit of a SPOILER if you keep reading but not a major one.The story line is pretty good so far, but still under development. I find it interesting, different, and quite funny that you begin the game with meat as the currency until your colony is built. Finally monsters/animals stop dropping gold.  I mean what animal carries a coin purse!"
