,Recommended,237870,11807474,"Posted: 21 August, 2014",all,bewatched,"This is an excellent game, and it is still in alpha. And I am downplaying my recommendation, as I want you to read this:- OpenWorld: You can freely go to any corner of the world. Difficulty is based on geographic location, so you may not be able to reach to other corner though. Almost every part of the world is modificable, and it is a HUGE world. (3D world, up and down also counts)- RPG: The is a gaming mode which I recommend, in were craftable items are adquired as rewards for missions. There is an impressive story (very linear though) which tells the separations of humankind between earth and mars, and how they come to colonize this planet. Also, you can have up to two  companions, and any number if you are on certain missions.- Crafting: There is a common and simple type of crafting, were if you have a recipe, and the items, you can synthetize the item. But what I recommend, is the advanced (or Build) crafting method, in which you can build YOUR OWN ship, boat, car, bike, sword, shield or gun. My first car was a wooden table with wheels, but now I have a TRON-like glider, a boat, and a five seated rover.- Graphics: Are great. I would have recommended the game without impressive graphics, but this game has AWESOME graphics. Granted, it is kind of idylic. But it looks f@#$ing great.- Base/Colony: You can build a colony, and have the NPC to move over. You can assign jobs to them, automatize the farming of vegetables. Put automatic weapons to defend the base and the NPC, etc, etc.Extra bits:- There is a JETPACK :D, and a GLIDER!!!!- Steam workshop allows to share what other people and you build in the advanced crafting interface. There is a ship build like Battlestar Galactica!!!- The Story is awesome. Even though is linear, is still an awesome story."
